{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882215242,"sessionID":"ses_2852c4c11ffe0Ez5NgMweWeY4P","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad415fa001whbSaho6K6FlKM","messageID":"msg_d7ad3f8f0001Fh0eIdPVLChIFt","sessionID":"ses_2852c4c11ffe0Ez5NgMweWeY4P","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-ab8465921c83411e86767e02800f11f4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-031/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-031/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) Specification\n2: \n3: ## Module: manifests\n4: \n5: ### ServiceAccount\n6: \n7: #### ServiceAccount Definition\n8: \n9: ```yaml\n10: apiVersion: v1\n11: kind: ServiceAccount\n12: metadata:\n13:   name: <service-account-name>\n14:   namespace: <namespace>\n15: ```\n16: \n17: **Parameters:**\n18: - `name`: ServiceAccount name\n19: - `namespace`: Kubernetes namespace\n20: \n21: ### Role\n22: \n23: #### Role Definition\n24: \n25: ```yaml\n26: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n27: kind: Role\n28: metadata:\n29:   name: <role-name>\n30:   namespace: <namespace>\n31: rules:\n32:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n33:     resources: [\"pods\", \"services\", \"configmaps\"]\n34:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n35: ```\n36: \n37: **Parameters:**\n38: - `name`: Role name\n39: - `namespace`: Kubernetes namespace\n40: - `rules`: List of policy rules\n41: \n42: ### RoleBinding\n43: \n44: #### RoleBinding Definition\n45: \n46: ```yaml\n47: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n48: kind: RoleBinding\n49: metadata:\n50:   name: <role-binding-name>\n51:   namespace: <namespace>\n52: subjects:\n53:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n54:     name: <service-account-name>\n55:     namespace: <namespace>\n56: roleRef:\n57:   kind: Role\n58:   name: <role-name>\n59:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n60: ```\n61: \n62: **Parameters:**\n63: - `name`: RoleBinding name\n64: - `namespace`: Kubernetes namespace\n65: - `subjects`: List of subjects (ServiceAccounts, Users, Groups)\n66: - `roleRef`: Reference to the Role\n67: \n68: ### ClusterRole (Optional)\n69: \n70: #### ClusterRole Definition\n71: \n72: ```yaml\n73: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n74: kind: ClusterRole\n75: metadata:\n76:   name: <cluster-role-name>\n77: rules:\n78:   - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n79:     resources: [\"nodes\", \"namespaces\"]\n80:     verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n81: ```\n82: \n83: **Parameters:**\n84: - `name`: ClusterRole name\n85: - `rules`: List of policy rules\n86: \n87: ### ClusterRoleBinding (Optional)\n88: \n89: #### ClusterRoleBinding Definition\n90: \n91: ```yaml\n92: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n93: kind: ClusterRoleBinding\n94: metadata:\n95:   name: <cluster-role-binding-name>\n96: subjects:\n97:   - kind: ServiceAccount\n98:     name: <service-account-name>\n99:     namespace: <namespace>\n100: roleRef:\n101:   kind: ClusterRole\n102:   name: <cluster-role-name>\n103:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n104: ```\n105: \n106: **Parameters:**\n107: - `name`: ClusterRoleBinding name\n108: - `subjects`: List of subjects\n109: - `roleRef`: Reference to the ClusterRole\n110: \n111: ## Common API Resources\n112: \n113: ### Core API (apiGroups: [\"\"])\n114: \n115: Common resources:\n116: - `pods`\n117: - `services`\n118: - `configmaps`\n119: - `secrets`\n120: - `persistentvolumeclaims`\n121: - `events`\n122: \n123: ### Apps API (apiGroups: [\"apps\"])\n124: \n125: Common resources:\n126: - `deployments`\n127: - `statefulsets`\n128: - `daemonsets`\n129: - `replicasets`\n130: \n131: ## Common Verbs\n132: \n133: - `get`, `list`, `watch` - Read operations\n134: - `create` - Create resources\n135: - `update`, `patch` - Update resources\n136: - `delete` - Delete resources\n137: - `*` - All operations\n138: \n139: ## Best Practices\n140: \n141: - Principle of least privilege\n142: - Namespace-scoped permissions where possible\n143: - Use specific resource names with `resourceNames` field for fine-grained control\n144: - Regular review of RBAC policies\n\n(End of file - total 144 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) Specification\n\n## Module: manifests\n\n### ServiceAccount\n\n#### ServiceAccount Definition\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: <service-account-name>\n  namespace: <namespace>\n```\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `name`: ServiceAccount name\n- `namespace`: Kubernetes namespace\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-031/spec.md","time":{"start":1775882215219,"end":1775882215240}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882215244,"sessionID":"ses_2852c4c11ffe0Ez5NgMweWeY4P","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad418fe001yGidExBo0GD9DY","messageID":"msg_d7ad3f8f0001Fh0eIdPVLChIFt","sessionID":"ses_2852c4c11ffe0Ez5NgMweWeY4P","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-83205edf03234c98b8c50f2a57a17fed","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## AR Metadata\n4: - **AR ID**: AR-031\n5: - **Title**: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding)\n6: - **Module**: manifests\n7: - **Language**: YAML\n8: - **Size**: M\n9: - **Status**: Implementation Required\n10: \n11: ## Purpose\n12: \n13: This delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for the Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) configuration in the AgentCube platform. It defines requirements for ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding, ClusterRole, and ClusterRoleBinding resources with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios to ensure proper Kubernetes RBAC setup for all components.\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: ServiceAccount definition and creation\n18: \n19: The system SHALL create ServiceAccount resources for AgentCube components with proper metadata and labels.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: ServiceAccount with required metadata\n22: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes namespace `agentcube` exists\n23: - **WHEN** a ServiceAccount YAML is applied\n24: - **THEN** the ServiceAccount SHALL have apiVersion: v1 and kind: ServiceAccount\n25: - **AND** the ServiceAccount SHALL have a name field\n26: - **AND** the ServiceAccount SHALL have a namespace field\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: ServiceAccount with custom labels\n29: - **GIVEN** a ServiceAccount definition\n30: - **WHEN** the metadata includes labels\n31: - **THEN** the labels SHALL be applied to the ServiceAccount\n32: - **AND** the labels SHALL include app: agentcube or component: <component-name>\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: ServiceAccount with automountServiceAccountToken\n35: - **GIVEN** a ServiceAccount definition\n36: - **WHEN** automountServiceAccountToken is set to false\n37: - **THEN** the ServiceAccount SHALL disable automatic token mounting\n38: - **AND** pods using this ServiceAccount SHALL not automatically mount the token\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: ServiceAccount with imagePullSecrets\n41: - **GIVEN** a ServiceAccount definition\n42: - **WHEN** imagePullSecrets are specified\n43: - **THEN** the ServiceAccount SHALL reference the specified secrets\n44: - **AND** pods using this ServiceAccount SHALL inherit the image pull secrets\n45: \n46: ### Requirement: Role definition with namespace-scoped permissions\n47: \n48: The system SHALL create Role resources with namespace-scoped permissions for AgentCube components.\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Role with core API resources\n51: - **GIVEN** a Role definition in a namespace\n52: - **WHEN** the Role is applied\n53: - **THEN** the Role SHALL have apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n54: - **AND** the Role SHALL have rules for core API resources (apiGroups: [\"\"])\n55: - **AND** the rules SHALL include resources: [\"pods\", \"services\", \"configmaps\"]\n56: - **AND** the rules SHALL include appropriate verbs (e.g., [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"])\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: Role with apps API resources\n59: - **GIVEN** a Role definition for workload management\n60: - **WHEN** the Role includes apps API permissions\n61: - **THEN** the rules SHALL include apiGroups: [\"apps\"]\n62: - **AND** the rules SHALL include resources: [\"deployments\", \"statefulsets\", \"daemonsets\"]\n63: - **AND** the rules SHALL include appropriate verbs for lifecycle management\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Role with custom resource permissions\n66: - **GIVEN** a Role definition for AgentCube CRDs\n67: - **WHEN** the Role includes CRD permissions\n68: - **THEN** the rules SHALL include the appropriate apiGroup (e.g., \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\")\n69: - **AND** the rules SHALL include the custom resource types\n70: - **AND** the rules SHALL include verbs for managing the custom resources\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: Role with resourceNames for fine-grained control\n73: - **GIVEN** a Role definition\n74: - **WHEN** resourceNames are specified in a rule\n75: - **THEN** the rule SHALL only apply to resources with matching names\n76: - **AND** the permission SHALL be restricted to specific named resources\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Role with multiple rules\n79: - **GIVEN** a Role definition\n80: - **WHEN** the Role includes multiple rules\n81: - **THEN** the Role SHALL aggregate all rules\n82: - **AND** the permissions SHALL be the union of all rules\n83: \n84: ### Requirement: RoleBinding linking ServiceAccount to Role\n85: \n86: The system SHALL create RoleBinding resources to link ServiceAccounts to Roles.\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: RoleBinding with ServiceAccount subject\n89: - **GIVEN** a RoleBinding definition\n90: - **WHEN** the RoleBinding is applied\n91: - **THEN** the RoleBinding SHALL have apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n92: - **AND** the subjects SHALL include kind: ServiceAccount\n93: - **AND** the subjects SHALL include the ServiceAccount name\n94: - **AND** the subjects SHALL include the namespace\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: RoleBinding with Role reference\n97: - **GIVEN** a RoleBinding definition\n98: - **WHEN** the roleRef is specified\n99: - **THEN** the roleRef SHALL have kind: Role\n100: - **AND** the roleRef SHALL have the Role name\n101: - **AND** the roleRef SHALL have apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: RoleBinding with multiple subjects\n104: - **GIVEN** a RoleBinding definition\n105: - **WHEN** multiple subjects are specified\n106: - **THEN** all subjects SHALL be bound to the Role\n107: - **AND** each subject SHALL have kind, name, and optionally namespace\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: RoleBinding in correct namespace\n110: - **GIVEN** a RoleBinding definition\n111: - **WHEN** the RoleBinding is created\n112: - **THEN** the RoleBinding SHALL be in the same namespace as the Role\n113: - **AND** the subjects SHALL reference ServiceAccounts in the same namespace (for namespace-scoped bindings)\n114: \n115: ### Requirement: ClusterRole for cluster-wide permissions\n116: \n117: The system SHALL create ClusterRole resources when cluster-wide permissions are required.\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: ClusterRole for node-level access\n120: - **GIVEN** a ClusterRole definition\n121: - **WHEN** the ClusterRole is applied\n122: - **THEN** the ClusterRole SHALL have apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n123: - **AND** the ClusterRole SHALL be cluster-scoped (no namespace)\n124: - **AND** the rules MAY include resources: [\"nodes\", \"namespaces\"]\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: ClusterRole for CRD management\n127: - **GIVEN** a ClusterRole definition for CRD access\n128: - **WHEN** the ClusterRole includes CRD permissions\n129: - **THEN** the rules SHALL include apiGroups: [\"apiextensions.k8s.io\"]\n130: - **AND** the rules SHALL include resources: [\"customresourcedefinitions\"]\n131: - **AND** the rules SHALL include appropriate verbs for CRD management\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: ClusterRole with nonResourceURLs\n134: - **GIVEN** a ClusterRole definition for API access\n135: - **WHEN** nonResourceURLs are specified\n136: - **THEN** the rules SHALL include nonResourceURLs for paths like /healthz, /metrics\n137: - **AND** the rules SHALL include verbs: [\"get\"]\n138: \n139: ### Requirement: ClusterRoleBinding for cluster-wide access\n140: \n141: The system SHALL create ClusterRoleBinding resources to link ServiceAccounts to ClusterRoles.\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: ClusterRoleBinding with ServiceAccount subject\n144: - **GIVEN** a ClusterRoleBinding definition\n145: - **WHEN** the ClusterRoleBinding is applied\n146: - **THEN** the ClusterRoleBinding SHALL have apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n147: - **AND** the ClusterRoleBinding SHALL be cluster-scoped (no namespace)\n148: - **AND** the subjects SHALL include kind: ServiceAccount\n149: - **AND** the subjects SHALL include the ServiceAccount name and namespace\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: ClusterRoleBinding with ClusterRole reference\n152: - **GIVEN** a ClusterRoleBinding definition\n153: - **WHEN** the roleRef is specified\n154: - **THEN** the roleRef SHALL have kind: ClusterRole\n155: - **AND** the roleRef SHALL have the ClusterRole name\n156: - **AND** the roleRef SHALL have apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n157: \n158: ### Requirement: Workload Manager RBAC configuration\n159: \n160: The system SHALL provide appropriate RBAC resources for the Workload Manager component.\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ServiceAccount\n163: - **GIVEN** the Workload Manager is deployed\n164: - **WHEN** the RBAC manifests are applied\n165: - **THEN** a ServiceAccount named workloadmanager SHALL be created\n166: - **AND** the ServiceAccount SHALL have appropriate labels\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRole permissions\n169: - **GIVEN** the Workload Manager ClusterRole\n170: - **WHEN** the permissions are inspected\n171: - **THEN** the ClusterRole SHALL include permissions for agent-sandbox resources\n172: - **AND** the ClusterRole SHALL include permissions for AgentCube runtime CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n173: - **AND** the ClusterRole SHALL include permissions for core workloads (pods, deployments)\n174: - **AND** the ClusterRole SHALL include permissions for secrets\n175: - **AND** the ClusterRole SHALL include permissions for authentication (tokenreviews)\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Workload Manager ClusterRoleBinding\n178: - **GIVEN** the Workload Manager RBAC configuration\n179: - **WHEN** the ClusterRoleBinding is applied\n180: - **THEN** the workloadmanager ServiceAccount SHALL be bound to the workloadmanager ClusterRole\n181: - **AND** the binding SHALL allow the Workload Manager to perform its required operations\n182: \n183: ### Requirement: Controller Manager RBAC configuration\n184: \n185: The system SHALL provide appropriate RBAC resources for the Controller Manager component.\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Controller Manager ServiceAccount\n188: - **GIVEN** the Controller Manager is deployed\n189: - **WHEN** the RBAC manifests are applied\n190: - **THEN** a ServiceAccount named agentcube-controller-manager SHALL be created\n191: - **AND** the ServiceAccount SHALL have appropriate labels\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: Controller Manager Role permissions\n194: - **GIVEN** the Controller Manager Role\n195: - **WHEN** the permissions are inspected\n196: - **THEN** the Role SHALL include permissions for managing AgentCube CRDs\n197: - **AND** the Role SHALL include permissions for watching and updating resources\n198: - **AND** the Role SHALL include permissions for creating and managing sub-resources\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Controller Manager RoleBinding\n201: - **GIVEN** the Controller Manager RBAC configuration\n202: - **WHEN** the RoleBinding is applied\n203: - **THEN** the agentcube-controller-manager ServiceAccount SHALL be bound to the appropriate Role\n204: - **AND** the binding SHALL be in the same namespace as the Controller Manager\n205: \n206: ### Requirement: Router RBAC configuration\n207: \n208: The system SHALL provide appropriate RBAC resources for the Router component.\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount\n211: - **GIVEN** the Router is deployed\n212: - **WHEN** the RBAC manifests are applied\n213: - **THEN** a ServiceAccount named agentcube-router SHALL be created (optional, depending on configuration)\n214: \n215: #### Scenario: Router Role for secrets access\n216: - **GIVEN** the Router needs to access secrets\n217: - **WHEN** the Router Role is defined\n218: - **THEN** the Role SHALL include permissions to get and list secrets in its namespace\n219: - **AND** the RoleBinding SHALL bind the ServiceAccount to this Role\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: Router RBAC is optional\n222: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with router.rbac.create=false\n223: - **WHEN** the manifests are applied\n224: - **THEN** no Router-specific RBAC resources SHALL be created\n225: - **AND** the Router SHALL use the default ServiceAccount\n226: \n227: ### Requirement: Principle of least privilege\n228: \n229: The system SHALL follow the principle of least privilege for all RBAC configurations.\n230: \n231: #### Scenario: Minimal permissions for Workload Manager\n232: - **GIVEN** the Workload Manager ClusterRole\n233: - **WHEN** the permissions are reviewed\n234: - **THEN** the permissions SHALL be limited to what the Workload Manager needs\n235: - **AND** unnecessary permissions SHALL NOT be granted\n236: - **AND** wildcard (*) permissions SHALL NOT be used unless absolutely necessary\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: Namespace-scoped permissions where possible\n239: - **GIVEN** a component that operates within a single namespace\n240: - **WHEN** RBAC is configured\n241: - **THEN** a Role and RoleBinding SHALL be used instead of ClusterRole and ClusterRoleBinding\n242: - **AND** permissions SHALL be restricted to the component's namespace\n243: \n244: #### Scenario: Specific verbs instead of wildcards\n245: - **GIVEN** a rule in a Role or ClusterRole\n246: - **WHEN** permissions are defined\n247: - **THEN** specific verbs (e.g., [\"get\", \"list\"]) SHALL be used\n248: - **AND** wildcard (*) verbs SHALL be avoided unless all operations are truly needed\n249: \n250: ### Requirement: RBAC resource validation\n251: \n252: The system SHALL ensure all RBAC resources are valid and functional.\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: ServiceAccount exists before use\n255: - **GIVEN** a Deployment references a ServiceAccount\n256: - **WHEN** the Deployment is created\n257: - **THEN** the referenced ServiceAccount MUST exist\n258: - **AND** the Deployment SHALL fail gracefully if the ServiceAccount does not exist\n259: \n260: #### Scenario: Role exists before binding\n261: - **GIVEN** a RoleBinding references a Role\n262: - **WHEN** the RoleBinding is applied\n263: - **THEN** the referenced Role MUST exist\n264: - **AND** the binding SHALL fail gracefully if the Role does not exist\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: Subject exists before binding\n267: - **GIVEN** a RoleBinding references a ServiceAccount\n268: - **WHEN** the RoleBinding is applied\n269: - **THEN** the referenced ServiceAccount MUST exist\n270: - **AND** the binding SHALL fail gracefully if the ServiceAccount does not exist\n271: \n272: #### Scenario: RBAC permissions are effective\n273: - **GIVEN** a pod is running with a specific ServiceAccount\n274: - **WHEN** the pod attempts to access a resource\n275: - **THEN** the access SHALL be granted only if the Role/ClusterRole permits it\n276: - **AND** the access SHALL be denied if the Role/ClusterRole does not permit it\n277: \n278: ### Requirement: RBAC documentation and labels\n279: \n280: The system SHALL provide proper documentation and labels for all RBAC resources.\n281: \n282: #### Scenario: ServiceAccount labels\n283: - **GIVEN** a ServiceAccount definition\n284: - **WHEN** labels are applied\n285: - **THEN** the ServiceAccount SHALL have an app label (e.g., app: agentcube)\n286: - **AND** the ServiceAccount SHALL have a component label (e.g., component: workload-manager)\n287: - **AND** the labels SHALL be consistent across all AgentCube resources\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: Role labels\n290: - **GIVEN** a Role definition\n291: - **WHEN** labels are applied\n292: - **THEN** the Role SHALL have labels indicating the component it serves\n293: - **AND** the labels SHALL be consistent with the ServiceAccount labels\n294: \n295: #### Scenario: RoleBinding annotations\n296: - **GIVEN** a RoleBinding definition\n297: - **WHEN** annotations are applied\n298: - **THEN** the annotations MAY include descriptions of the permission grant\n299: - **AND** the annotations MAY include references to related documentation\n300: \n301: ### Requirement: RBAC upgrade and migration\n302: \n303: The system SHALL support RBAC configuration upgrades without breaking existing permissions.\n304: \n305: #### Scenario: Role upgrade preserves existing permissions\n306: - **GIVEN** an existing Role is in use\n307: - **WHEN** the Role is updated\n308: - **THEN** existing permissions SHALL NOT be removed without reason\n309: - **AND** new permissions MAY be added as needed\n310: - **AND** the upgrade SHALL not break existing workloads\n311: \n312: #### Scenario: ServiceAccount upgrade\n313: - **GIVEN** an existing ServiceAccount is in use\n314: - **WHEN** the ServiceAccount is updated\n315: - **THEN** the ServiceAccount name SHALL NOT change\n316: - **AND** the update SHALL not break existing bindings\n317: \n318: #### Scenario: RBAC removal is graceful\n319: - **GIVEN** RBAC resources are being removed\n320: - **WHEN** a Role or ClusterRole is deleted\n321: - **THEN** dependent bindings SHALL be deleted or updated\n322: - **AND** the removal SHALL not leave orphaned bindings\n323: \n324: ### Requirement: RBAC testing and validation\n325: \n326: The system SHALL support testing and validation of RBAC configurations.\n327: \n328: #### Scenario: Verify ServiceAccount token is mounted\n329: - **GIVEN** a pod is running with a ServiceAccount\n330: - **WHEN** the pod's token is checked\n331: - **THEN** the token SHALL be mounted at /var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\n332: - **AND** the token SHALL be valid for authentication\n333: \n334: #### Scenario: Verify Role permissions are granted\n335: - **GIVEN** a pod with a ServiceAccount bound to a Role\n336: - **WHEN** the pod attempts a permitted operation\n337: - **THEN** the operation SHALL succeed\n338: - **AND** the pod SHALL not receive a Forbidden error\n339: \n340: #### Scenario: Verify Role permissions are denied\n341: - **GIVEN** a pod with a ServiceAccount bound to a Role\n342: - **WHEN** the pod attempts a non-permitted operation\n343: - **THEN** the operation SHALL fail\n344: - **AND** the pod SHALL receive a Forbidden error\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: Verify ClusterRole permissions are granted\n347: - **GIVEN** a pod with a ServiceAccount bound to a ClusterRole\n348: - **WHEN** the pod attempts a cluster-wide permitted operation\n349: - **THEN** the operation SHALL succeed\n350: - **AND** the pod SHALL not receive a Forbidden error\n351: \n352: ### Requirement: RBAC for monitoring and observability\n353: \n354: The system SHALL provide appropriate RBAC resources for monitoring and observability components.\n355: \n356: #### Scenario: ServiceAccount for monitoring\n357: - **GIVEN** monitoring components need to access AgentCube resources\n358: - **WHEN** RBAC is configured\n359: - **THEN** a separate ServiceAccount MAY be created for monitoring\n360: - **AND** the ServiceAccount SHALL have minimal read-only permissions\n361: \n362: #### Scenario: Role for metrics collection\n363: - **GIVEN** a monitoring system collects metrics\n364: - **WHEN** the Role is defined\n365: - **THEN** the Role SHALL include permissions to get and list resources for metrics\n366: - **AND** the Role SHALL NOT include permissions to modify resources\n367: \n368: ### Requirement: RBAC configuration via Helm values\n369: \n370: The system SHALL support RBAC configuration through Helm chart values.\n371: \n372: #### Scenario: RBAC creation enabled by default\n373: - **GIVEN** the Helm chart with default values\n374: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n375: - **THEN** rbac.create SHALL default to true\n376: - **AND** all RBAC resources SHALL be created\n377: \n378: #### Scenario: RBAC creation disabled via values\n379: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with rbac.create=false\n380: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n381: - **THEN** no RBAC resources SHALL be created\n382: - **AND** components SHALL use default ServiceAccount\n383: \n384: #### Scenario: Custom ServiceAccount name via values\n385: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with custom serviceAccount name\n386: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n387: - **THEN** the custom ServiceAccount name SHALL be used\n388: - **AND** all bindings SHALL reference the custom name\n389: \n390: #### Scenario: Existing ServiceAccount via values\n391: - **GIVEN** values.yaml with serviceAccount.create=false and serviceAccount.name=existing-sa\n392: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n393: - **THEN** no new ServiceAccount SHALL be created\n394: - **AND** the existing ServiceAccount SHALL be referenced\n395: - **AND** bindings SHALL use the existing ServiceAccount\n396: \n397: ---\n398: \n399: ## Backward Compatibility\n400: \n401: This delta specification defines RBAC configuration for the AgentCube platform. The RBAC resources are new additions that provide proper access control for all components. Existing deployments without RBAC will continue to work using the default ServiceAccount, but it is strongly recommended to use the RBAC configuration for production deployments.\n402: \n403: ## Dependencies\n404: \n405: This delta specification depends on:\n406: - Kubernetes 1.20+ (RBAC API v1)\n407: - Base design document: `design.md`\n408: - Base specification document: `deployment/spec.md`\n409: - AR: AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding)\n410: - AR: AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values (for Helm-based RBAC configuration)\n411: \n412: ## Breaking Changes\n413: \n414: None. This delta specification defines new RBAC resources that are optional via configuration (e.g., rbac.create Helm value). Existing deployments without RBAC will continue to work.\n415: \n416: ## Security Considerations\n417: \n418: 1. **Principle of Least Privilege**: All RBAC configurations follow the principle of least privilege, granting only the minimum permissions required.\n419: 2. **Namespace Isolation**: Where possible, namespace-scoped Roles and RoleBindings are used instead of cluster-wide permissions.\n420: 3. **Service Account Tokens**: Automounting of ServiceAccount tokens can be disabled for components that don't need them.\n421: 4. **Secret Access**: Access to secrets is carefully controlled and limited to components that require it.\n422: 5. **Audit**: RBAC configurations should be audited regularly to ensure they remain appropriate.\n423: 6. **Wildcard Permissions**: Wildcard (*) permissions are avoided unless absolutely necessary.\n424: 7. **Cluster-Wide Access**: ClusterRoles and ClusterRoleBindings are used sparingly and only when necessary.\n425: \n426: ## Testing Strategy\n427: \n428: ### Unit Tests\n429: - Verify ServiceAccount YAML syntax and structure\n430: - Verify Role YAML syntax and rule definitions\n431: - Verify RoleBinding YAML syntax and references\n432: - Verify ClusterRole YAML syntax and rule definitions\n433: - Verify ClusterRoleBinding YAML syntax and references\n434: \n435: ### Integration Tests\n436: - Test that ServiceAccounts are created successfully\n437: - Test that Roles grant the correct permissions\n438: - Test that RoleBindings correctly bind ServiceAccounts to Roles\n439: - Test that ClusterRoles grant cluster-wide permissions\n440: - Test that ClusterRoleBindings correctly bind ServiceAccounts to ClusterRoles\n441: \n442: ### Permission Tests\n443: - Test that pods with the correct ServiceAccount can access permitted resources\n444: - Test that pods are denied access to non-permitted resources\n445: - Test that the principle of least privilege is enforced\n446: - Test that namespace-scoped permissions are enforced\n447: - Test that cluster-wide permissions are enforced correctly\n448: \n449: ### Upgrade Tests\n450: - Test that RBAC resources can be upgraded without breaking existing permissions\n451: - Test that RBAC resources can be removed gracefully\n452: - Test that changes to RBAC resources are applied correctly\n453: \n454: ### Helm Chart Tests\n455: - Test that RBAC resources are created by default\n456: - Test that RBAC resources can be disabled via values\n457: - Test that custom ServiceAccount names work correctly\n458: - Test that existing ServiceAccounts can be referenced\n459: - Test that RBAC resources are properly labeled\n\n(End of file - total 459 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) Delta Specification\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-031\n- **Title**: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding)\n- **Module**: manifests\n- **Language**: YAML\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for the Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) configuration in the AgentCube platform. It defines requirements for ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding, ClusterRole, and ClusterRoleBinding resources with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios to ensure proper Kubernetes RBAC setup for all components.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: ServiceAccount definition and creation\n\nThe system SHALL create ServiceAccount resources for AgentCube components with proper metadata and labels.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-031/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775882215222,"end":1775882215242}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882215248,"sessionID":"ses_2852c4c11ffe0Ez5NgMweWeY4P","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad41c1d001qe2Xmg2K1iuybC","messageID":"msg_d7ad3f8f0001Fh0eIdPVLChIFt","sessionID":"ses_2852c4c11ffe0Ez5NgMweWeY4P","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-89e3c2d47fbc49dda63aafcd466ad509","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/router/rbac.yaml"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/router/rbac.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {{- if and .Values.router.enabled .Values.router.rbac.create }}\n2: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n3: kind: Role\n4: metadata:\n5:   name: {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n6:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n7:   labels:\n8:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n9:     app.kubernetes.io/component: router\n10: rules:\n11: - apiGroups:\n12:   - \"\"\n13:   resources:\n14:   - secrets\n15:   verbs:\n16:   - get\n17:   - list\n18:   - watch\n19: ---\n20: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n21: kind: RoleBinding\n22: metadata:\n23:   name: {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n24:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n25:   labels:\n26:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n27:     app.kubernetes.io/component: router\n28: roleRef:\n29:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n30:   kind: Role\n31:   name: {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n32: subjects:\n33: - kind: ServiceAccount\n34:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.router.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n35:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n36: {{- end }}\n\n(End of file - total 36 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{{- if and .Values.router.enabled .Values.router.rbac.create }}\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Role\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: router\nrules:\n- apiGroups:\n  - \"\"\n  resources:\n  - secrets\n  verbs:\n  - get\n  - list\n  - watch\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/router/rbac.yaml","time":{"start":1775882215224,"end":1775882215247}}}}
