{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882315614,"sessionID":"ses_2852c4c11ffe0Ez5NgMweWeY4P","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad5a6fe001JH1hHwXplQN2k9","messageID":"msg_d7ad48ec30016v2I0vD7oGFICQ","sessionID":"ses_2852c4c11ffe0Ez5NgMweWeY4P","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-8b83607b7100481da84a1791f1e69b87","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) Tasks\n\n**Module**: `manifests`\n**Language**: YAML\n**Size**: M\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Review existing Workload Manager ServiceAccount template\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n- [ ] Verify template includes proper Helm conditionals (enabled and serviceAccount.create)\n- [ ] Verify template uses correct helper functions (serviceAccountName, namespace, labels)\n- [ ] Verify component label is set to workload-manager\n- [ ] Verify annotations are conditionally included\n- [ ] Document any issues or missing elements\n\n**Verification**: Template follows best practices and matches component pattern\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Review existing Workload Manager RBAC template\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml\n- [ ] Verify ClusterRole is defined with proper metadata\n- [ ] Verify ClusterRoleBinding is defined with proper metadata\n- [ ] Verify rules reference .Values.rbac.clusterRole.rules\n- [ ] Verify subjects reference correct ServiceAccount\n- [ ] Verify roleRef references correct ClusterRole\n- [ ] Document any issues or missing elements\n\n**Verification**: Template matches delta-spec.md requirements for Workload Manager\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Complete Workload Manager ClusterRole rules in values.yaml\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/values.yaml rbac.clusterRole.rules section\n- [ ] Verify rules include permissions for agent-sandbox resources\n- [ ] Verify rules include permissions for AgentRuntime CRDs (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes)\n- [ ] Verify rules include permissions for CodeInterpreter CRDs (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters)\n- [ ] Verify rules include permissions for status subresources\n- [ ] Verify rules include permissions for core workloads (pods, services, configmaps)\n- [ ] Verify rules include permissions for secrets (get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete)\n- [ ] Verify rules include permissions for events (create, patch)\n- [ ] Verify rules follow principle of least privilege (no wildcards unless necessary)\n- [ ] Add any missing permissions based on delta-spec.md requirements\n\n**Verification**: Workload Manager ClusterRole has all required permissions with minimal privileges\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Review existing Controller Manager ServiceAccount template\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n- [ ] Verify template includes proper Helm conditionals\n- [ ] Verify template uses correct helper functions\n- [ ] Verify component label is set to controller-manager\n- [ ] Verify annotations are conditionally included\n- [ ] Document any issues or missing elements\n\n**Verification**: Template follows best practices and matches component pattern\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Review existing Controller Manager RBAC template\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml\n- [ ] Verify Role is defined with proper metadata\n- [ ] Verify RoleBinding is defined with proper metadata\n- [ ] Verify rules reference .Values.controllerManager.rbac.rules\n- [ ] Verify subjects reference correct ServiceAccount\n- [ ] Verify roleRef references correct Role\n- [ ] Document any issues or missing elements\n\n**Verification**: Template matches delta-spec.md requirements for Controller Manager\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Define Controller Manager Role rules in values.yaml\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/values.yaml controllerManager.rbac.rules section\n- [ ] Define rules for managing AgentCube CRDs (agentruntimes, codeinterpreters)\n- [ ] Define rules for watching and updating resources\n- [ ] Define rules for creating and managing sub-resources (configmaps, secrets, events)\n- [ ] Define rules for status subresources\n- [ ] Ensure rules are namespace-scoped (no cluster-wide permissions)\n- [ ] Follow principle of least privilege\n- [ ] Add rule for getting and updating pods status\n- [ ] Add rule for creating events\n\n**Verification**: Controller Manager Role has all required permissions with minimal privileges\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Review existing Router ServiceAccount template\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/router/serviceaccount.yaml\n- [ ] Verify template includes proper Helm conditionals\n- [ ] Verify template uses correct helper functions\n- [ ] Verify component label is set to router\n- [ ] Verify annotations are conditionally included\n- [ ] Document any issues or missing elements\n\n**Verification**: Template follows best practices and matches component pattern\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Review existing Router RBAC template\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/router/rbac.yaml\n- [ ] Verify Role is defined with proper metadata\n- [ ] Verify RoleBinding is defined with proper metadata\n- [ ] Verify rules include permissions for secrets (get, list, watch)\n- [ ] Verify subjects reference correct ServiceAccount\n- [ ] Verify roleRef references correct Role\n- [ ] Document any issues or missing elements\n\n**Verification**: Template matches delta-spec.md requirements for Router\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Verify Router RBAC is optional via values.yaml\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/values.yaml router.rbac section\n- [ ] Verify router.rbac.create defaults to true\n- [ ] Verify Router RBAC templates check .Values.router.rbac.create\n- [ ] Verify Router ServiceAccount creation is controlled by .Values.router.serviceAccount.create\n- [ ] Verify templates support custom ServiceAccount name via .Values.router.serviceAccount.name\n- [ ] Document any missing configuration options\n\n**Verification**: Router RBAC can be disabled and customized via Helm values\n\n---\n\n### Task 10: Verify Workload Manager RBAC is optional via values.yaml\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/values.yaml workloadManager.rbac section\n- [ ] Verify workloadManager.rbac.create defaults to true\n- [ ] Verify Workload Manager RBAC templates check .Values.workloadManager.rbac.create\n- [ ] Verify Workload Manager ServiceAccount creation is controlled by .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.create\n- [ ] Verify templates support custom ServiceAccount name via .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.name\n- [ ] Document any missing configuration options\n\n**Verification**: Workload Manager RBAC can be disabled and customized via Helm values\n\n---\n\n### Task 11: Verify Controller Manager RBAC is optional via values.yaml\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/values.yaml controllerManager.rbac section\n- [ ] Verify controllerManager.rbac.create defaults to true\n- [ ] Verify Controller Manager RBAC templates check .Values.controllerManager.rbac.create\n- [ ] Verify Controller Manager ServiceAccount creation is controlled by .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.create\n- [ ] Verify templates support custom ServiceAccount name via .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.name\n- [ ] Document any missing configuration options\n\n**Verification**: Controller Manager RBAC can be disabled and customized via Helm values\n\n---\n\n### Task 12: Add automountServiceAccountToken option to ServiceAccount templates\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n- [ ] Add automountServiceAccountToken field based on .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.automountServiceAccountToken\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n- [ ] Add automountServiceAccountToken field based on .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.automountServiceAccountToken\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/router/serviceaccount.yaml\n- [ ] Add automountServiceAccountToken field based on .Values.router.serviceAccount.automountServiceAccountToken\n- [ ] Add default values to values.yaml for automountServiceAccountToken (default: true)\n\n**Verification**: All ServiceAccount templates support configurable token automounting\n\n---\n\n### Task 13: Add imagePullSecrets option to ServiceAccount templates\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n- [ ] Add imagePullSecrets field based on .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.imagePullSecrets\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n- [ ] Add imagePullSecrets field based on .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.imagePullSecrets\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/router/serviceaccount.yaml\n- [ ] Add imagePullSecrets field based on .Values.router.serviceAccount.imagePullSecrets\n- [ ] Add default values to values.yaml for imagePullSecrets (default: [])\n\n**Verification**: All ServiceAccount templates support configurable image pull secrets\n\n---\n\n### Task 14: Verify RBAC helper functions exist in _helpers.tpl\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/_helpers.tpl\n- [ ] Verify serviceAccountName helper exists for workloadManager\n- [ ] Verify serviceAccountName helper exists for controllerManager\n- [ ] Verify serviceAccountName helper exists for router\n- [ ] Verify helpers handle custom ServiceAccount names correctly\n- [ ] Verify helpers handle default ServiceAccount names correctly\n- [ ] Document any missing helper functions\n\n**Verification**: All required RBAC helper functions are defined and working\n\n---\n\n### Task 15: Add annotations to Role and ClusterRole metadata\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml\n- [ ] Add annotations section to ClusterRole metadata\n- [ ] Add an