ller Manager, Router)\n- [ ] Document how to enable/disable RBAC via Helm values\n- [ ] Document how to use custom ServiceAccounts\n- [ ] Document principle of least privilege\n- [ ] Provide examples of RBAC configuration\n\n**Verification**: RBAC documentation is complete and accurate\n\n---\n\n### Task 19: Create RBAC testing checklist\n- [ ] Create manifests/RBAC_TESTING.md\n- [ ] Document how to verify ServiceAccount creation\n- [ ] Document how to verify Role/ClusterRole permissions\n- [ ] Document how to verify RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding\n- [ ] Document how to test permissions are granted\n- [ ] Document how to test permissions are denied\n- [ ] Document how to verify least privilege principle\n\n**Verification**: RBAC testing checklist is comprehensive\n\n---\n\n### Task 20: Validate YAML syntax for all RBAC templates\n- [ ] Run Helm template on manifests/charts/agentcube with default values\n- [ ] Verify all RBAC resources are generated correctly\n- [ ] Run helm lint on manifests/charts/agentcube\n- [ ] Fix any YAML syntax errors\n- [ ] Run kubeconform or similar validator on generated manifests\n- [ ] Verify all RBAC resources pass validation\n\n**Verification**: All RBAC templates have valid YAML syntax\n\n---\n\n### Task 21: Test RBAC with default values\n- [ ] Create test namespace\n- [ ] Install Helm chart with default values (rbac.create=true for all components)\n- [ ] Verify Workload Manager ServiceAccount is created\n- [ ] Verify Workload Manager ClusterRole is created with correct rules\n- [ ] Verify Workload Manager ClusterRoleBinding is created\n- [ ] Verify Controller Manager ServiceAccount is created\n- [ ] Verify Controller Manager Role is created with correct rules\n- [ ] Verify Controller Manager RoleBinding is created\n- [ ] Verify Router ServiceAccount is created\n- [ ] Verify Router Role is created with correct rules\n- [ ] Verify Router RoleBinding is created\n\n**Verification**: All RBAC resources are created correctly with default v